import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['dir'], data['speed'])
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and wind direction?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist2d(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], bins=(80, 60), cmap='viridis')
    plt.colorbar(label='Frequency')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the geographical distribution of wind vectors?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
